column1: Notes: both Iarea and Rarea are the sum of all islands/reefs represented by each island (i.e. combined within the same set of connected shallow MODIS pixels).
Lon/lat are always within the island contour line and may differ from lon/lat from the Nunn database where positions can be over the ocean (e.g. center of atolls).
Ref Nunn database: Nunn et al. (2016). Classifying Pacific islands. Geoscience Letters 3(1) https://doi.org/10.1186/s40562-016-0041-8
Reference: Messié et al. (2022). Basin-scale biogeochemical and ecological impacts of islands in the tropical Pacific Ocean. Nature Geoscience https://doi.org/10.1038/s41561-022-00957-8.

column6: Island area obtained either from the Nunn database or from the island contour (km2)
column7: Island reef area calculated from GEBCO (< 500 m resolution) as the area of pixels above 30 m depth (including emerged lands km2(
